# Mastering React Hooks

React Hooks have revolutionized how we write React components. Let's explore some common hooks and best practices.

## useState

```javascript
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
```

## useEffect

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  document.title = `Count: ${count}`;
}, [count]);
```

## Custom Hooks

```javascript
function useWindowSize() {
  const [size, setSize] = useState({ width: 0, height: 0 });

  useEffect(() => {
    function updateSize() {
      setSize({ width: window.innerWidth, height: window.innerHeight });
    }
    window.addEventListener('resize', updateSize);
    updateSize();
    return () => window.removeEventListener('resize', updateSize);
  }, []);

  return size;
}
```

Hooks make React development more intuitive and fun!

# Modern CSS Techniques

CSS has evolved significantly. Let's look at some modern techniques that make web design easier and more powerful.

## CSS Grid

```css
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
}
```

## CSS Custom Properties

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #3498db;
  --secondary-color: #2ecc71;
}

.button {
  background: var(--primary-color);
}
```

## Modern Selectors

```css
.card:is(:hover, :focus) {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
```

Modern CSS is amazing!
